-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Arkema, London Mining 
-- 
-- Tue Jul 08, 2014 12:59AM EDT
-- None



July 8 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Arkema and London Mining, on Tuesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Arkema <AKE.PA>: JP Morgan cuts to underweight from overweight * London Mining <LOND.L>: Barclays raises to equal weight from underweightFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Tuesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. See bottom of the table for sector changes. * African Minerals <AMIq.L>: Barclays cuts target to 115p from 170p; rating underweight * Arkema <AKE.PA>: JP Morgan cuts to underweight from overweight * Arkema <AKE.PA>: JP Morgan cuts target price to 55 euros from 86 euros * BNP Paribas <BNPP.PA>: S&P Capital IQ cuts target to 55 euros from 60 euros; rating hold * Darty <DRTY.L>: Nomura adjusts target price to 100p from 67p; rating neutral * Domino Printing Sciences <DOPR.L>: UBS cuts target price to 690p from 840p; rating buy * London Mining <LOND.L>: Barclays raises to equal weight from underweight * London Mining <LOND.L>: Barclays raises target price to 80p from 75p * Optimal Payments <OPAY.L>: Barclays raises target to 600p from 525p; rating overweight * Petrofac Ltd <PFC.L>: Berenberg cuts target price to 1440p from 1740p; rating buy * Rio Tinto <RIO.L>: Barclays raises to overweight from equal weight  * Rio Tinto <RIO.L>: Barclays raises target price to 3600p from 3350p * Stagecoach Group <SGC.L>: Jefferies raises price target to 415p from 350p; rating hold * Storebrand <STB.OL>: JP Morgan raises target to Nok 44.30 from Nok 42.30; overweight  * Temenos <TEMN.S>: Barclays raises target price to Sfr 41 from Sfr 36; rating overweight